{"version":1,"entries":{"person_1468779_translations":{"at":1772469923704,"data":{"id":1468779,"translations":[{"iso_3166_1":"US","iso_639_1":"en","name":"English","english_name":"English","data":{"biography":"Jimmy O. Yang (born June 11, 1987) is a stand-up comedian and actor. He stars as Jian-Yang on HBO's Silicon Valley (2014), Bernard Tai in the film Crazy Rich Asians and as real-life hero Dun Meng in the film Patriots Day (2016). As a stand-up, he performed on The Arsenio Hall Show and received a rare standing ovation. Jimmy can also be seen on season 9 of It's Always Sunny in Philadelphia as Charlie's dear friend Tang-See. Jimmy is fluent in three Chinese dialects: Mandarin, Cantonese, Shanghainese.","name":"Jimmy O. Yang","primary":true}},{"iso_3166_1":"KR","iso_639_1":"ko","name":"한국어/조선말","english_name":"Korean","data":{"biography":"","name":"지미 O. 양","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"BR","iso_639_1":"pt","name":"Português","english_name":"Portuguese","data":{"biography":"Jimmy O. Yang é um ator, comediante e escritor norte-americano de Hong Kong, mais conhecido por protagonizar Jian-Yang na série de comédia da HBO Silicon Valley.","name":"","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"CN","iso_639_1":"zh","name":"普通话","english_name":"Mandarin","data":{"biography":"欧阳万成是一名香港裔美国男演员、单口喜剧演员和作家，以在HBO喜剧《硅谷》饰演靳阳而知名。 1987年6月11日，欧阳万成在香港出生，曾经在香港华仁书院接受一年的教育，13岁时随家人移民美国，希望他借此受到更好的教育。","name":"欧阳万成","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"UA","iso_639_1":"uk","name":"Український","english_name":"Ukrainian","data":{"biography":"","name":"Джиммі О. Ян","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"HK","iso_639_1":"zh","name":"普通话","english_name":"Mandarin","data":{"biography":"歐陽萬成是一名香港裔美國男演員、單口喜劇演員和作家，以在 HBO 喜劇《矽谷》飾演靳陽而知名。\n\n1987 年 6 月 11 日，歐陽萬成在香港出生，曾經在香港華仁書院接受一年的教育，13 歲時隨家人移民美國，希望他藉此受到更好的教育。","name":"歐陽萬成","primary":false}}]}},"person_15170_translations":{"at":1772469923918,"data":{"id":15170,"translations":[{"iso_3166_1":"CN","iso_639_1":"zh","name":"普通话","english_name":"Mandarin","data":{"biography":"中国演员，毕业于北京电影学院表演系90级，在校期间担任班长。\n\n1999年，因电影《洗澡》中出演二明为人所知，并且凭借此片相继获得2000第7届北京大学生电影节最佳男演员奖、2000年第5届中国长春电影节最佳男配角奖等等总共四个奖项。\n\n1992年，代表作《葛老爷子》获中国长春国际电影节“长春银杯奖”。\n\n1999年，《美丽新世界》获得1999年第19届夏威夷国际电影节最佳男主角奖。\n\n2004年，《别了温哥华》获得2004年第四届电视节“双十佳”“十佳”演员奖。\n\n2007年，《5颗子弹》获得2007第26届中国电影金鸡奖最佳男配角提名。\n\n2009年，《我的唐朝兄弟》获得2010第6届中美电影节最佳男主角奖、2010第2届英国万像国际华语电影节最佳男演员奖。\n\n2009年，《满堂爹娘》获得2010年2010春季电视剧互联网盛典最佳男演员奖。\n\n2011年，《誓言今生》获得2012年第8届华鼎奖中国近代革命题材电视剧最佳男演员。\n\n2013年，主演贾樟柯导演电影《天注定》，此片入围第66届戛纳国际电影节正式竞赛单元，5月17日在戛纳全球首映，荣膺最佳编剧奖。\n\n2015年，姜武出任2015海峡国际微电影节形象大使。","name":"姜武","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"US","iso_639_1":"en","name":"English","english_name":"English","data":{"biography":"Jiang Wu was born on November 14, 1967 in Tangshan, China. He has graduated from Beijing Film Academy.\n\nHe starred in Zhang Yimou's To Live (1994), and Zhang Yang's Shower (1999). He is the younger brother of director, screenwriter and actor Jiang Wen.","name":"Jiang Wu","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"TW","iso_639_1":"zh","name":"普通话","english_name":"Mandarin","data":{"biography":"","name":"姜武","primary":true}},{"iso_3166_1":"VN","iso_639_1":"vi","name":"Tiếng Việt","english_name":"Vietnamese","data":{"biography":"","name":"Khương Vũ","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"DE","iso_639_1":"de","name":"Deutsch","english_name":"German","data":{"biography":"","name":"Jiang Wu","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"HK","iso_639_1":"zh","name":"普通话","english_name":"Mandarin","data":{"biography":"中國演員，畢業於北京電影學院表演系 90 級，在校期間擔任班長。\n\n1999 年，因電影《洗澡》中出演二明為人所知，並且憑藉此片相繼獲得 2000 第 7 屆北京大學生電影節最佳男演員獎、2000 年第 5 屆中國長春電影節最佳男配角獎等等總共四個獎項。\n\n1992 年，代表作《葛老爺子》獲中國長春國際電影節“長春銀盃獎”。\n\n1999 年，《美麗新世界》獲得 1999 年第 19 屆夏威夷國際電影節最佳男主角獎。\n\n2004 年，《別了温哥華》獲得 2004 年第四屆電視節“雙十佳”“十佳”演員獎。\n\n2007 年，《5 顆子彈》獲得 2007 第 26 屆中國電影金雞獎最佳男配角提名。\n\n2009 年，《我的唐朝兄弟》獲得 2010 第 6 屆中美電影節最佳男主角獎、2010 第 2 屆英國萬像國際華語電影節最佳男演員獎。\n\n2009 年，《滿堂爹孃》獲得 2010 年 2010 春季電視劇網際網路盛典最佳男演員獎。\n\n2011 年，《誓言今生》獲得 2012 年第 8 屆華鼎獎中國近代革命題材電視劇最佳男演員。\n\n2013 年，主演賈樟柯導演電影《天註定》，此片入圍第 66 屆戛納國際電影節正式競賽單元，5 月 17 日在戛納全球首映，榮膺最佳編劇獎。\n\n2015 年，姜武出任 2015 海峽國際微電影節形象大使。","name":"姜武","primary":false}}]}},"person_1897274_translations":{"at":1772469925486,"data":{"id":1897274,"translations":[{"iso_3166_1":"US","iso_639_1":"en","name":"English","english_name":"English","data":{"biography":"Peng Yuchang (born October 25, 1994, in Xinyu, Jiangxi Province, China) is an acclaimed Chinese actor known for his versatility, emotional depth, and charming screen presence. He graduated from the Puppet Performance Department of the Shanghai Theater Academy, an unusual major that showcases his creative range and willingness to explore unconventional paths in performance.\n\nPeng made waves in the Chinese film industry with breakout roles in films such as Our Shining Days (2017), Go Brother! (2018), An Elephant Sitting Still (2018), and Leap (2020), where he portrayed young Chen Zhonghe, showcasing his talent for heartfelt and inspiring portrayals. His performance as Wei Bu in An Elephant Sitting Still brought international attention for its powerful portrayal of youth alienation and despair.\n\nOn television, Peng has appeared in popular series such as The Prince of Tennis (2019), Lady of Law (2022), and I Am Nobody (2023–2025), playing lead characters like Zhang Chulan across multiple seasons. With over 60 acting credits to his name, he continues to expand his footprint across drama, comedy, fantasy, and variety programming.\n\nPeng Yuchang is widely admired for his grounded demeanor, strong work ethic, and ability to transition seamlessly between lighthearted and dramatic roles. His contribution to modern Chinese storytelling places him among the most promising talents of his generation.","name":"Peng Yuchang","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"CN","iso_639_1":"zh","name":"普通话","english_name":"Mandarin","data":{"biography":"彭昱畅，1994年10月25日出生于江西省新余市，毕业于上海戏剧学院木偶表演系，中国内地男演员","name":"彭昱畅","primary":true}},{"iso_3166_1":"MY","iso_639_1":"my","name":"","english_name":"Burmese","data":{"biography":""